SIMPLE: horsechestnut
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Horsechestnut
<hw>Horse`chest"nut</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The large
nutlike seed of a species of <gen>Aesculus</gen> (<spn>Aesculus
Hippocastanum</spn>), formerly ground, and fed to horses, whence the
name. The seed is not considered edible by humans.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The tree itself (<spn>Aesculus
hippocastanum</spn>), which was brought from Constantinople in the
beginning of the sixteenth century, and is now common in the temperate
zones of both hemispheres; it has palmate leaves and large clusters of
white to red flowers followed by brown shiny inedible seeds. The native
American species is also called <altname>buckeye</altname> and
<altname>conker</altname>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>horsecloth</ent>⟦br⟧
